# React Native Firebase Notes App

A simple note-taking app built with React Native and Firebase.

## Table of Contents

- [Installation](#installation)
- [Firebase Configuration](#firebase-configuration)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Features](#features)
- [Folder Structure](#folder-structure)
- [Dependencies](#dependencies)

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo.git
Navigate to the project directory:

bash
Copy code
cd your-repo
Install dependencies:

bash
Copy code
npm install

2. Firebase Configuration
Create a Firebase project on the Firebase Console.

Copy the Firebase configuration object from the Firebase Console.

Replace the placeholder configuration in firebase/index.js with your actual Firebase configuration:

javascript
Copy code
const firebaseConfig = {
  // Your Firebase configuration goes here
};
Usage
Run the app on your local development environment:

bash
Copy code
npm start
Follow the instructions provided by Expo to open the app on an emulator or a physical device.

3. Features
Create, edit, and delete notes
Mark notes as checked or unchecked
Seamless integration with Firebase for data storage
Folder Structure
components: React components used in the app.
auth: Authentication-related components.
firebase: Firebase configuration and utilities.
screens: Screens or pages of the app.

4. Dependencies
@react-navigation/native: Navigation library for React Native.
@react-navigation/stack: Stack navigator for React Navigation.
firebase: Firebase SDK for JavaScript.
react: React library.
react-native: React Native framework.
react-native-async-storage/async-storage: Asynchronous storage for React Native.
react-native-gesture-handler: Gesture handler for React Native.
react-native-reanimated: React Native library for smooth animations.
react-native-screens: Native navigation container for React Native.
expo: Expo development framework for React Native.